column13: This elegant hotel lies in its own beautiful well-tended gardens. The ambience created in the hotel attracts a high rate of repeat visitors and the level of service here is top notch — you'll be impressed by the little touches, like speedy check-in, nightly turn-down service and Champagne cocktails at the intimate Bobster's Champagne Bar. During the day, you can choose from a range of non-motorised water sports and treatments at the tranquil spa, or simply relax by the pool or in the gallery lounge with afternoon tea overlooking the ocean. The private white sand beach is one of the best on the island with a specially built lagoon to create a calm swimming area for kids. You will find superb cuisine in two restaurants for both buffet dining and à la carte dining.

Tidewater Beach Resort | Panama City, Florida Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: If you’re heading for Florida’s fabulous Panhandle, it’s probably for the beaches — so a spot right on the sands of Panama City Beach is pretty hard to rival. Along one of the biggest private beaches (said to cover more than two football fields of sand), this high-rise shoots up from the shoreline to give you the best in beachfront apartment living. Each of the private condos inside is unique, but they all share a collection of handy holiday extras — including two beachfront lagoon pools, an indoor pool, a fitness centre, a games room, and a handful of hot tubs. There’s space in your condo to cook, dine, and lounge about, but you’re also a stroll from Pier Park’s shops and restaurants if you fancy forgoing the washing up and dining out.

Enchanted Island Resort | Seychelles, Indian Ocean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: If there’s even the slightest bit of ‘Robinson Crusoe’ in you, it’s sure to come out at the romantic JA Enchanted Island Resort. But this is doing ‘castaway’ like an A-lister. Home to a mere ten luxurious villas, this little private island sits in Sainte Anne National Marine Park. Your exclusive villa has a charming creole design and features a private infinity pool, outdoor bathroom, deck and gazebo, and a private walkway down to the beach. And, although you may not have a ‘Man Friday’, you do have a butler at your service to put loungers on the beach for you, bring you a refreshing drink or arrange a kayak for you. There’s a restaurant by the hotel’s clifftop pool where the chef's on hand to chat about the delectable local dishes, or you could opt for private dining on your villa’s terrace. And, if that’s not enough extravagance, the resort's spa offers more in its oceanfront treatment pavilions. This island hideaway is the ultimate in privacy and relaxation for couples.

Magellan Sutera Harbour Resort | Kota Kinabalu, Borneo Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Set against a majestic mountain backdrop and overlooking the South China Sea, the Magellan is set over 384 acres and offers guests a complete holiday experience. Every amenity, every comfort, and every excitement you could wish for is on hand – ranging from water sports galore down at the beach to the inimitable luxury of the world-class Mandara Spa. Guest rooms are luxuriously appointed, overlooking either perfectly manicured lawns or the ocean, with family rooms ideal for those who need more space to stretch out in. Golf aficionados will appreciate a few rounds on the Graham Marsh designed championship course or grab your partner and head down to the squash courts. An Olympic-sized swimming pools means you can get a few decent laps in or simply splash around with the kids in the fun pool. Dining is extensive too with Italian restaurant Ferdinand’s listed as one of Malaysia’s best restaurants! Alternatively, there’s a sumptuous buffet at Five Sails or feast on wood-fired pizzas beside the pool at Al Fresco’s. Choose your own pace at Magellan, it can be as lively as you want it to be or a relaxing haven you’ll want to return to again and again.

A beautiful resort, it also enjoys a luxurious setting in 30-acres of lush gardens, framed by majestic ancient rain trees. Some of the world’s most recognisable names have holidayed here, including celebrity author Barbara Cartland and the former King of Cambodia. A definite attraction is CHI, The Spa, the largest and most luxuriously appointed in Penang. There’s also award-winning cuisine served at the Ferringi Grill, which boasts a wine cellar and cigar menu, or indulge in buffet delights at the Spice Market Café.

column7: Savannah Beach | Barbados, Caribbean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Exclusive to Virgin Holidays in the UK, the Savannah Beach is a beautiful resort offering a warm Caribbean welcome and some of the best accommodation on the south coast. Set right on the beach, within a UNESCO heritage site, with easy access to the historic Garrison area, you can walk across the road to watch the changing of the sentry ceremony at the main guard house. When it comes to school holidays, children and teens are extremely well catered for at this hotel, there is a fantastic family entertainment centre to keep even the most energetic children entertained, featuring the Pirates Cove Kids' Club for the smaller ones and Finn’s Surf Lodge for the older one. If you are here to relax, this is a perfect choice for an authentic Caribbean break, simply chill out by one of two swimming pools, on the beach, at one of the bars and three restaurants, or book yourself a relaxing massage at the spa. Feel like a VIP by adding a Club Room package to your room booking — with highlights such as the exclusive VIP decking area with reserved sun loungers and food and drinks service. The Virgin Holidays exclusive Concierge Lounge is ideal for some shade or when you want to connect with home. There really is something for everyone here.

column7: Sunscape Splash Montego Bay | Montego Bay, Jamaica Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: A large resort on its own private peninsula with over 1,800 ft of white sand beach, the all Sunscape Splash Montego Bay has a fantastic range of activities available for everyone to enjoy an Unlimited-Fun® getaway. Families will particularly appreciate The Explorer's Club, for kids aged 3-12 years, and the Core Zone Teens Club with pool tables, video games and a host of activities. Both facilities are located in the Pirates’ Paradise Waterpark with two giant slides, Blackbeard’s Lazy River and a Pirates ship! While the kids are enjoying themselves, you can sneak off to the spa for a relaxing treatment. Remember though, you are not just limited to the extensive list of on-site activities, as the Sunscape Montego Bay Jamaica is ideally located within reach of several local points of interest including Dunn's River Falls, Dolphin Cove and five unique golf courses for the golfing enthusiasts amongst you. With five restaurants to choose from you can savour a variety of international cuisine and come dark, venture to one of five bars and kick back in true Jamaican style, while listening to some authentic live music, sipping on a refreshing cocktail — perfect! Whatsmore, Sun Club Guests have access to two additional restaurants and bars, so treat yourself to an upgraded package for exclusive benefits and tuck into breakfast at the Terrace Restaurant or for dinner, feast upon some Italian cuisine at Da Mario.

column7: Centara Villas Samui | Koh Samui, Thailand Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Escape to the private world of Centara Villas Samui. Gently nestled on Natien Beach on the south coast of Koh Samui, you can unwind in privacy on a beautiful white sand beach. You will be greeted with warm friendly smiles from a team of staff that will offer a dedicated service to meet your every need and requirement. The Thai-style Villas are dotted amongst the tropical foliage of a gentle hillside leading down to the beautiful beach, the interiors a lovely combination of light linens and dark flooring. For something a little special, upgrade to a Spa Villa with its own Jacuzzi or a Pool Villa complete with an outdoor plunge pool. The Spa Cenvaree provides traditional aromatherapy and therapeutic massages. If you fancy getting out and about, there are special day trips available to Mutsum Island for fantastic coral reef snorkelling and fishing. You are also just a short ride from three of Koh Samui’s Buddhist wats, Wat Khunaram, Wat Samret, and Wat Laem Saw.

Dreams Punta Cana Resort & Spa | Punta Cana, Dominican Republic Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Aptly named, this Unlimited-Luxury® resort is a dream come true! Almost everything is included, including gourmet meals, top-shelf drinks and sporting amenities galore. Accommodation is also second to none, each room is graciously appointed and luxurious equipped with plenty of space to relax in. Make your holiday extra special and upgrade to a room that includes Preferred Club Privileges, you’ll feel like a true VIP! Water sports are on the agenda all day every day. There are also plenty of dry-land activities but the jewel in the crown has got to be the free-form pool, it’s incredible. One of the largest in the Dominican Republic, it stretches from the lobby all the way down to the pristine beach and is sure to be a hit with just about everyone. A visit (or two) to the world-class spa is a must, indulge in a chocolate body wrap or enjoy a water lily after-sun soothing wrap — sublime! The kids are in for a treat too. At the Explorer’s Club time flies with treasure hunts to keep them busy, sandcastle contests, hiking and arts and crafts. Teens aren’t left out either; they’ve their very own place to hang — the Core Zone — complete with rock climbing wall, basketball, video games and disco nights. The dining at Dreams is unrivalled; there are so many restaurants to choose from. As for the bars, there are ten of them, some cosy and laid-back, others with a more happening vibe. And last but not least, don your glad rags and head to the casino for a night full of sophistication and a sprinkle of good luck.

column13: The Bay Gardens Beach Resort and Spa is situated on St Lucia's beautiful Reduit Beach and nestled in Rodney Bay Village, St Lucia's entertainment capital. There's a welcoming lagoon-style swimming pool with Jacuzzis and a sun deck in the middle, plus two restaurants and bars, including the new Sea Grapes Restaurant for that special occasion or simply to have fun and relax with the family. A more than welcome addition, Splash Island Water Park is the first open water park and perfect for families with children from age 6 up, it's fast becoming a firm favourite with holidaymakers to this fabulous sunshine island!

Anantara Bophut Koh Samui Resort | Koh Samui, Thailand Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Overlooking a tranquil stretch of sand, guests can enjoy inimitable luxury at the Anantara Bophut, coupled with world renowned Thai hospitality. If you want to take it easy, that’s fine, top up your tan on the beach, read a good book beside the pool or treat yourself to an Ayurvedic healing ritual at the world-class spa. There are lessons aplenty here with Thai cookery classes available, cocktail mixing classes and fruit carving classes. A state-of-the-art fitness centre ensures the body stays beautiful or indulge in a fun game of tennis with your partner and new-found friends. Youngsters are kept busy too at the Baan Ling Noi Kids' Club – a happy environment with an impressive range of exciting activities. A few minutes away is a small fishing village, lovely for an early evening stroll. For dinner, head to Full Moon to feast on chargrilled cuisine beside the sea. High Tide with its garden veranda serves fusion cuisine in a relaxed island atmosphere. Afternoon tea is served in the Library whilst the chic environs of Eclipse offers an extensive menu of cocktails. Private gourmet barbeques can also be arranged.

column7: The Mirage | Strip, Las Vegas Hotel | Virgin Holidays
Hard Rock Hotel & Casino Punta Cana | Punta Cana, Dominican Republic Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Whichever room you decide to stay in at this iconic hotel, you’re going to feel like a rock star — guaranteed! Spacious, indulgent, decadent — those are all words that can be used to describe accommodation here, with liquor dispensers and double hydro tubs standard throughout. Feel like a superstar, however, in the Rock Star Suite — not only is it huge, it contains drum kits and authentic memorabilia, two electric guitars courtesy of Aerosmith and Paul Stanley no less! Elsewhere in this incredible resort you’ll find 11 swimming pools, there’s the Family Pool, the Isla Pool with Latin-flavoured beats, the Central Pool where everyone gathers and the Sax Pool for peace and quiet. You can also work out to your hearts content at Body Rock fitness centre or chill at Rock Spa®, undoubtedly the finest in the Caribbean complete with hydrotherapy centre, lagoons, whirlpools, steam rooms and cutting edge ice room. Whilst parents are at play, the little ones are too, at their very own kids' club featuring educational, interactive and all-out fun activities. Dining is fun at the Hard Rock too, with breakfast cocktails served at Cafetto. There’s also Italian, Mexican, Chinese and Japanese cuisine to get stuck into and bars galore with DJs, amazing views and top-shelf liquors. Not only boasting one of the biggest casinos in the Caribbean, there’s ORO Nightclub too — located inside the casino and most definitely the gem of the Caribbean!

column7: Cotton House | St Vincent and the Grenadines, Caribbean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: On a private island, surrounded by 13-acres of tropical gardens, Cotton House is a glorious collection of garden and sea-facing rooms and suites, built in old-Caribbean style, some with private verandas and plunge pools. The beach is just a short walk away and will take your breath away — consisting of azure waters and fine white sands, it’s the ideal place to either relax in the shade or indulge in a few water sports. The Veranda Restaurant is highly acclaimed and the wine list excellent. Alternatively, head to the Great Room Bar with its cooling fans, lime washed woods and signature colonial style. The Beach Café offers fresh fish, lobster (in season) and light dishes — perfect for lunch. Afterwards, enjoy a snooze under the palm trees or work up an appetite for dinner with a few rounds of tennis. Every week there’s a cocktail party to get to know those who are holidaying with you and movie nights on Friday and Saturday are a treat. Venture further afield and you’ll find Firefly and Basil’s Bar, lively venues, where you can join the locals in partying the night away.

column7: Secrets Wild Orchid Montego Bay | Montego Bay, Jamaica Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: An adult-only resort, Secrets Wild Orchid Montego Bay is Unlimited-Luxury® with an incredible range of amenities at your disposal. Designed in contemporary style and splashed with indigenous art, all suites are supremely comfortable with gorgeous four-poster beds, a full entertainment system and a Whirlpool tub. Upgrade to Preferred Club for private pool access amongst other luxurious benefits. There are opportunities galore for relaxing but if you’re feeling active, you’re in luck, there’s also plenty to keep you busy including tennis, basketball and volleyball. For all pursuits aquatic, head down to the beach, taking advantage of your complimentary scuba diving lesson in the swimming pool and the complimentary non-motorised water sports of course! A state-of-the-art fitness centre may also tempt you or treat yourself to an hour or two at the lavish Secrets Spa by Pevonia with its oceanfront massage cabanas. Nights are lively too with an open-air theatre hosting some spectacular live music performances. In addition to enjoying all the benefits Secrets Wild Orchid has to offer, guests have the opportunity to utilise all of the privileges available at their sister property, Secrets St James, conveniently located next door! Alternatively, snuggle up and enjoy a movie together on the beach or head to Desires Music Lounge for dancing. There are seven gourmet à la carte restaurants to choose from, each one specialising in dishes from around the world. For Mexican à la carte there’s El Patio, or reserve a table at the Tepenyaki table in Himitsu for exciting Pan-Asian cuisine. There’s also Oceana, for delicious fresh seafood, Bordeaux for French à la carte and Portofino for Italian favourites, all of which offer outside dining. Nine bars compliment the range of restaurants, including a Cigar and Piano Bar with an easy-going, relaxed atmosphere and the Beach Bar serving exotic cocktails against a background of crashing waves.

Savannah Beach | Barbados, Caribbean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Exclusive to Virgin Holidays in the UK, the Savannah Beach is a beautiful resort offering a warm Caribbean welcome and some of the best accommodation on the south coast. Set right on the beach, within a UNESCO heritage site, with easy access to the historic Garrison area, you can walk across the road to watch the changing of the sentry ceremony at the main guard house. When it comes to school holidays, children and teens are extremely well catered for at this hotel, there is a fantastic family entertainment centre to keep even the most energetic children entertained, featuring the Pirates Cove Kids' Club for the smaller ones and Finn’s Surf Lodge for the older one. If you are here to relax, this is a perfect choice for an authentic Caribbean break, simply chill out by one of two swimming pools, on the beach, at one of the bars and three restaurants, or book yourself a relaxing massage at the spa. Feel like a VIP by adding a Club Room package to your room booking — with highlights such as the exclusive VIP decking area with reserved sun loungers and food and drinks service. The Virgin Holidays exclusive Concierge Lounge is ideal for some shade or when you want to connect with home. There really is something for everyone here.

column13: If its peace and serenity you want, you’ve come to the right place! Tucked away in a secluded location, the Jewel Paradise Cove is nothing short of idyllic. Strictly for adults only, it’s all inclusive too, not just meals, snacks and premium drinks but water sports galore as well — it really doesn't get much better than this. Hang on, yes it does, green fees at the 18-hole championship Runaway Bay Golf Club are also complimentary. So whether you’re an aficionado or a complete novice, get stuck in. When you’re not playing, relax at Radiant Spa, a sanctuary in every sense of the word. The fitness centre is also world-class, making this an ideal choice for those interested in health and beauty. Accommodation is another treat — all rooms are contemporary with state-of-the-art technology. If you’re on honeymoon, upgrade to a Junior Suite — you’ll enjoy personalised butler service if you do, helping to make your stay even more special. When it comes to dining, there are seven dining experiences to choose from, ranging from the laid-back, beach-side Aquamarina to the highly romantic Platinum, where you can feast on Caribbean delights. Enjoy a moonlit stroll after dinner perhaps or head to Bling! — a lively disco bar with tunes to keep you dancing until the early hours.

Galley Bay Resort & Spa | Antigua, Caribbean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Set on one of Antigua's many beautiful beaches, this exclusive adults-only hideaway offers guests a fabulous combination of superior service, Caribbean cuisine and rustic luxury in a very natural setting. Much of the architecture here is inspired by the French artist Gauguin. The charming, refurbished individual suites have their own splash pool and are surrounded by lush gardens and views of the lagoon. There is a peaceful, natural lagoon which is host to rare birds, pelicans and herons. There are three excellent open-air restaurants, all beachfront, offering intimate, candlelit dining of excellent quality. Ismay's Restaurant, offers a higher quality dining experience to be shared for that special occasion, whilst the more laid-back Barefoot Grill is a great place to enjoy a tasty quesadilla made with resort grown produce. At sunset, hors d'oeuvres are served at the bar, which overlooks the sea from under its Tahitian-style roof. There are activities such as fishing on the lagoon, non-motorised water sports and a recently expanded gym, but reclining with a novel on the beachfront deck from the library is equally as popular.

column13: One of Varadero’s most family centric hangouts, Sol Palmeras keeps every member of your party happy. It’s got all the tropical scenery you’ve come to the Caribbean for – with a boast-worthy spot on one of Cuba’s most famous beaches. It’s got the lagoon pools, with their palm and palapas accessories, and a mini-pool in the family zone for young guests. It’s got poolside rooms near the action and bungalows near the beach for those after a more remote retreat. And its list of children’s attractions is as long as your sun-bronzed arm – from mini-discos to a bouncy castle, mini-golf, and computer games.

column7: Waves Hotel & Spa by Elegant Hotels | Barbados, Caribbean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Taking all inclusive to another level, the Waves Hotel & Spa by Elegant Hotels doesn’t just include essentials like dining and WiFi, it lays on luxuries like water sports, spa treatments and yoga. From cocktail mixology to rum tasting, you’ll never be short of entertainment. You can even ‘add on’ bucket list experiences like swimming with sea turtles. Its restaurants take you from the Mediterranean to Asia but, as a new member of Elegant Hotels, you can now dine at their select west coast sister hotels too, travelling there by complimentary water taxi. It’s not all about getting off the sunbed though — nobody will mind if you laze away days at the spa, by the two pools, or on its Platinum West Coast beach, and the complimentary Beach and Pool Ambassador Service guarantee true unadulterated relaxation.

column7: Disney's Animal Kingdom Lodge | Walt Disney World, Orlando Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Explore the riches of Africa at Disney's Animal Kingdom Lodge. The adventure of a jungle safari comes alive before your eyes with lush surroundings, showcasing the grandeur of this mighty kingdom. Many rooms overlook the beautiful savannas, from which you can spot grazing zebra, giraffes and gazelles roaming free in natural environments. The hotel offers a wide range of activities honouring these animals, aimed at every age range. Go on a cultural safari, see animals play at dusk, with the benefit of night vision, and watch handlers feed pelicans and flamingos. Younger members of the family can even try being junior researchers for a day! Cultural representatives from Africa are on hand to share information with you about their homeland, giving you a unique insight into its fascinating environment. A very special place indeed, the rhythm of tribal drums, the exquisite cuisine, the rich settings and the lure of authentic African treasures, combine to celebrate the beauty and wonders of this vast continent in a way the whole family can appreciate and enjoy.

column13: The St James’s Club Morgan Bay encapsulates everything typically Caribbean boasting a wealth of activities and a great choice of restaurants in a vibrant and refreshingly casual setting. With plenty of great on-site facilities to keep the whole family entertained, the kids' club, four pools, beach games, sailing and water-skiing make for a fun day; and we all know – happy kids equal happy parents! They too are well catered for, with fully equipped gym, daily activities, fitness classes for adults and the Tranquility Body & Soul Spa, you’ll always be spoilt for choice in and around this beautiful ‘Eden of the Caribbean’ island. If you do decide to venture further afield, on your return don’t forget to take advantage of the great selection of distinct restaurants and evening entertainment and of course, the weekly Fete Bor la Mer beach party every Wednesday; which includes local entertainment and traditional dishes, at this lively All-Inclusive resort. Then just sit back, relax and embrace the chilled, Caribbean pace of life.

column13: Lapping it up in the true ‘lap’ of luxury, Hodges Bay Resort & Spa is a world away from the cookie cutter beach hotels that crop up around the Caribbean. Designed to be different, every element of this 9-acre estate is refined and relaxing. Its gloriously green gardens are matched by whiter-than-white sands, its crisp contemporary architecture cocoons upscale interiors, and its features are beyond high-end. There are two swimming pools — including an adult-only infinity pool overlooking the bay, surrounded by plush sun-loungers and poolside cabanas, the ultimate way to catch some Caribbean rays and relax in an adult-only oasis. Not forgetting the beach and pool Ambassador Service of course, with dedicated staff on hand to tend to your every whim, from polishing your sunglasses to anticipating your need for another iced tropical drink. The beach is made even better with the non-motorised water sports on offer. Little guests get to feel like VIPs too with their Flying Fish Kids Club and Connect Teens Lounge. And the five bars here include that island must, a rum bar with its own Sommelier to guarantee you a true taste of Antigua.

column7: Mauna Kea Beach Hotel | Big Island, Hawaii Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: A statement of pure luxury, Mauna Kea Beach Hotel was the most expensive hotel ever built when it opened in 1965. It’s maintained its high-class status ever since with dramatic renovations creating oversized rooms while still keeping it’s mid-century modern magic. Consistently winning awards for its scenic golf course, oceanfront tennis club, and incredible dining, the white sands of Kauna’oa Bay are the stage for this luxury Big Island retreat. Mauna Kea’s decadent dining prime location is Manta & Pavilion Wine Bar, where you can take the stone path to see Manta Rays ‘dance’ at night, but it’s the authentic Hawaiian twists of the hotel that make this place truly special with lei-making tutorials, lu’au parties with local dishes and fire dancing, beachside clambakes with dancing on the sands and Sunday Brunch Buffets with legendary dessert tables.

column7: Cap Maison | St Lucia, Caribbean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: At the tip of the island, the former sugar plantation that is now St Lucia’s Cap Estate is blessed with unparalleled panoramic views of where Caribbean Sea meets Atlantic Ocean. The boutique resort of Cap Maison makes the very best of these views and is designed to feel as if you are visiting your own private Caribbean residence. For dining with a view look no further than the award-winning destination restaurant, Cliff at Cap, with an innovative French West Indies fusion menu. It’s strategically placed atop the Cliff with a sunset lookout for happy hour cocktails. The pool adjacent to the restaurant enjoys the same views from its sun deck and there is an adjacent secluded beach cove appropriately named The Naked Fisherman beach restaurant. Take the 90 steps down to the sand and you’ll find a rustic beach bar serving up lunch time grills, freshly squeezed juices and wonderful rum concoctions. Kayaks, snorkels and Hobie cats are complimentary to guests or you can take some tuition for a fee. Spa Maison and the fitness centre are available for further rejuvenating body and mind; on hand there is a pilates/yoga instructor and a fitness trainer to lead morning jogs across the estate. The Cap Estate’s rolling hills have also become home to the 18-hole St Lucia Golf & Country Club. Guests at Cap Maison benefit from concessionary golf at this beautiful and challenging championship course which extends virtually from the Caribbean to the Atlantic coastlines (a complimentary shuttle takes approx. 5-minutes).

column13: In an idyllic location, overlooking one of Antigua’s best beaches, with fine white sand and turquoise waters. Lively in atmosphere, there’s always plenty to do, including water sports, pool volleyball and beach games, perhaps even an impromptu game of cricket on the sand late afternoon. Kids have their very own club, promising a fun packed itinerary of activities whilst parents can head to the quiet pool or spa for some much-deserved relaxation and pampering. There are five restaurants in total, serving everything from International favourites to Caribbean delights and an Italian selection at the Bocciolo Restaurant and Bar.

column7: Conrad Maldives Rangali Island | Maldives, Indian Ocean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: At this oasis of luxury, you can relish two palm-fringed tropical islands, as well as a separate Spa Retreat. The resort is linked by a 500-metre footbridge — stroll across and admire the underwater life from above or take a dhoni or beach buggy if that's more your style. Choose from three different luxury resort experiences: beautifully furnished Beach Villas on the main Rangalifinolhi Island, home to the main pool, kids pool and water sports centre; amazing, thatch-roofed Water Villas perched on stilts over the shallow waters off Rangali Island, where you'll also find the Quiet Zone pool; or luxurious Retreat Water Villas, with their own treatment room and jacuzzi, part of the only Destination Spa in the Maldives. You'll also be spoilt for choice when it comes to dining, with eight restaurants across the two islands. Set five metres below the surface of the Indian Ocean is the underwater restaurant, Ithaa, with fantastic 180º views of the surrounding coral gardens and serving exquisite European cuisine.

Hodges Bay Resort & Spa by Elegant Hotels | Antigua, Caribbean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Lapping it up in the true ‘lap’ of luxury, Hodges Bay Resort & Spa is a world away from the cookie cutter beach hotels that crop up around the Caribbean. Designed to be different, every element of this 9-acre estate is refined and relaxing. Its gloriously green gardens are matched by whiter-than-white sands, its crisp contemporary architecture cocoons upscale interiors, and its features are beyond high-end. There are two swimming pools — including an adult-only infinity pool overlooking the bay, surrounded by plush sun-loungers and poolside cabanas, the ultimate way to catch some Caribbean rays and relax in an adult-only oasis. Not forgetting the beach and pool Ambassador Service of course, with dedicated staff on hand to tend to your every whim, from polishing your sunglasses to anticipating your need for another iced tropical drink. The beach is made even better with the non-motorised water sports on offer. Little guests get to feel like VIPs too with their Flying Fish Kids Club and Connect Teens Lounge. And the five bars here include that island must, a rum bar with its own Sommelier to guarantee you a true taste of Antigua.

column13: This wonderful hotel is in an idyllic spot, up on the secluded Northeast coast, and everyone gets a well-appointed, lovely suite with its own oversized, furnished verandah. The rooms are all in single-storey, open-planned suites scattered throughout the beautifully landscaped, 30-acre resort which leads down to two sandy beaches. Natural materials have been used in the suites' classic Caribbean design, with gabled roofs and timber-clad frames. Learn Hobie Cat sailing, enjoy beach volleyball, explore the nature trails of the national park or admire the limestone formations of Devil's Bridge.

column13: The Grand Oasis Riviera Maya offers a wealth of natural beauty and serenity, with a white sand beach, spa with yoga classes, and a choice of four swimming pools. From 2019, this property will be changing it's name, and will be known as Grand Oasis Tulum. You're spoilt for choice here - with 9 restaurants, 8 bars, a range of watersports and a golf course nearby - or perhaps snorkelling on one of the longest and most vibrant coral reefs in Mexico is more your idea of how to spend your holiday. Despite the vast range of things to do at the hotel, it's not completely cut off - you're just 10 miles from the Mayan archeological site of Tulum, and a short trip from Chichen Itza - recently named one of the New Seven Wonders of the World.

column13: Steal precious time together at Rendezvous, exclusively for couples. This all-inclusive boutique resort is set on a magnificent 2-mile stretch of unspoilt beach where couples can take a break from from the stresses and strains of everyday life and concentrate on each other. With two pools, a lazy river and a beautiful rockery garden as well as a Spa in the Water Garden, couples can indulge in some well-earned relaxation. They call Rendezvous 'The Holiday of Stolen Time' and it's easy to see why. You'll find plenty of spots to lie back in a hammock, one of the double beach cabanas or in the secluded water garden with lazy river and water waiter service.

column7: Secrets Cap Cana Resort & Spa | Punta Cana, Dominican Republic Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: One of the island’s hottest new hotel openings, the adults-only Secrets Cap Cana Resort & Spa is set in the private gated community of Cap Cana, directly on the magnificent sugar-sand Juanillo Beach. Within close proximity to the Cap Cana protected marina and two renowned golf courses, designed by golf legend Jack Nicklaus, you can spend the morning marveling at the super yachts and finish the day off with a round of golf alongside the Caribbean sea. The coastlines are also considered among the best spots in the world for fishing and deep-water diving. It is not hard to see that Secrets Cap Cana is the epitome of luxury and its exclusive setting is matched by its guarantee of Unlimited-Luxury®, including 24-hour gourmet dining, limitless top shelf spirits, wines, beers and soft drinks, 24-hour Concierge service, movies on the beach, and weekly parties. It even has waiter service on its palm-studded white sandy beach and around its incredible infinity lagoon pool. You can experience a different dining venue for every day of the week, six of them a la carte restaurants along with a buffet restaurant. But, with every room a Junior Suite, you might prefer to make the most of the all-inclusive 24-hour room service.

column7: The Beach Club | Antigua, Caribbean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Situated upon a beautiful stretch of beach, you’ll be treated especially well by the friendly, helpful staff here. The rooms are spacious, overlook the beach and out to sea and the bath tub on ground floor rooms only is perfect for a romantic soak for two. You’ve got two beaches to choose from, one on the calm bay side, where you can also try your hand at a wide range of free non-motorised water sports and the other benefiting from refreshing ocean breezes to cool you as you soak up the rays. Coco’s Restaurant has an airy, spacious feel and overlooks the beach, serving an excellent all day menu. Its bar is the perfect spot to seek some shade during the day or enjoy a relaxing pre-dinner drink as the sun goes down. Children are in their element here as the kids’ club is great fun — parents will appreciate the break to enjoy a game of tennis or perhaps pump some iron in the fitness centre. Obviously, lounging around the pool terrace at Coco’s, drinking a coconut crush is another option, especially if topping up your tan is high on your holiday ‘to do’ list!

column13: This beautifully positioned adults-only resort has a range of individual pastel-painted cottages with some of the most spectacular views on the island. The main restaurant is on three different levels and enjoys alfresco breezes, while Sheer Rocks restaurant offers delicious gourmet cuisine with individual booths for extra privacy all overlooking the beautiful bay. There's a 'Wellness Cottage' that offers a range of wonderful treatments. On either side of the bluff lie two beautiful beaches, with a third within walking (or kayaking) distance!

Hyatt Zilara Rose Hall | Montego Bay, Jamaica Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: A contemporary hideaway, the Hyatt Zilara Rose Hall occupies a prime location, nestled between Jamaica’s famous Blue Mountain ridge and the turquoise waters of the Caribbean. An adults-only retreat offering "Service from the Heart!", the atmosphere is gorgeously laid-back, ensuring plenty of rest and relaxation on the agenda. The private beach is nearly a mile long with swimmable coves to be alone in. All the usual sporting pastimes are on offer including beach volleyball, tennis, basketball. When the day fades, there are restaurants and bars galore, not just those belonging to the Zilara but to the family friendly sister hotel, the Ziva, as well, offering 12 distinctly different restaurants to choose from. Feast on cuisines from all around the world, including French, Pan-Asian, Italian, Brazilian and Caribbean. For pre-dinner drinks we recommend the Zilara’s very own Portionz — paying homage to the famed White Witch of Rose Hall — the cocktails are magical!

column7: Doubletree Sonoma | Sonoma, Napa Valley Wine Region Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Distinctly Mediterranean in style, the DoubleTree by Hilton Sonoma Wine Country offers a relaxing resort escape in the middle of California’s world-famous wine country. If you’re a golf enthusiast as well as a wine enthusiast, you’re in luck; it’s surrounded by two 18-hole PGA certified Championship golf courses with spectacular views of the fairways enjoyed from some of the rooms. Other top-notch amenities include a delightful courtyard heated swimming pool, perfect for lounging by with a glass of local wine and a fitness centre with state-of-the-art equipment. A complimentary wine and cheese reception every Friday evening from May-Oct, is a great opportunity to meet fellow guests and staff, comparing vineyard notes perhaps and sightseeing tips. When it comes to dining, Bacchus is a joy, with its casually elegant atmosphere and al-fresco heated patio overlooking the Sonoma Mountains. Drawing from an abundance of local produce, the menu is creative and ever changing with wines perfectly paired to your meal. Afterwards, enjoy a nightcap in the lobby bar, marvelling on another perfect day!

column7: Hilton Rose Hall Resort & Spa | Montego Bay, Jamaica Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Lying on a beautiful, long stretch of private beach, this tropical resort is situated in 400 lush acres of an 18th-century sugar plantation. There’s a large main swimming pool, but everyone (kids' especially) loves the Sugar Mill Falls Waterpark, which is the largest in Jamaica. Why not grab a tube and float down the ‘lazy river’ or try one of the slides. Water sports are available from the brand new beach, overlooking the sparkling Caribbean Sea. There’s also a daily kids' club, leaving you with time to recharge in the full-service spa, or why not try out the Championship golf course, tennis and the popular aerobics classes. A variety of restaurant options with fine dining and sophisticated wine lists are on-site. The most romantic restaurant is the Three Palms, up on the hillside looking down over the hotel and the sea beyond.

column13: All the customary Caribbean luxuries come as standard here: squeaky soft white sands, impossibly blue sea, tropical gardens, and Jamaican entertainment. But Sunscape Cove has a few extra tricks up its short summery sleeves. Things like its setting, on a private peninsula wrapped by Montego Bay Marine Park, with its protected swimming spots and snorkelling. Promising ‘Unlimited-Fun®’ and an automatic ‘Sun Club’ upgrade, you get endless land and water activities, unlimited drinks, and 24-hour dining, all completely complimentary, and covered by eight eateries, seven bars and room service. You even get access-all-areas at Sunscape Splash next door, where pleasures include the incredible Pirate’s Paradise Waterpark. In fact, little VIPs are well-catered for at Sunscape Cove, with a science, nature and exploration themed Explorer’s Club, teens’ Core Zone, and in-room cartoons, milk and cookies all included.

Hyatt Ziva Rose Hall | Montego Bay, Jamaica Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Following a recent multi-million dollar renovation, the All-Inclusive Hyatt Ziva Rose Hall offers even more luxurious accommodation than before. There’s a huge range of room options to choose from, all with gorgeous views of the surrounding tropical gardens or the ocean. You can even choose a room with direct pool access or upgrade to Club Level for special privileges. Tucked between the mountains and the sea, it’s hailed as a paradise of rest, relaxation and recreation and rightly so! Prepare yourself for "Service from the Heart!" — a genuine warm Jamaican welcome and service with a smile. For something a little special, head to the spa for a relaxing massage or body wrap. Whilst you do, the kids can play with other youngsters at their very own club, building sandcastles or getting stuck into some arts and crafts. With regards to restaurants, you’ll find plenty on your doorstep — at the Ziva, there’s a whole range of world cuisines to choose from! Visit Italy one night, Brazil the next and Asia when the mood takes you. We doubt very much you’ll be homesick but if you are, head to Union Jack’z — an English tavern that not only serves pub favourites but also features live music too. Alternatively, sip on cocktails on the rooftop at the Moroccan-inspired Fez.

column7: The House by Elegant Hotels | Barbados, Caribbean Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Set on a pristine stretch of white sand on Barbados’ West Coast, The House is the beachside version of a hip downtown hotel. On a design front its combination of smooth lines of teak, crisp white love seats and ambient torchlights set a mood that is suitably exotic. Yet it’s a beautifully intimate place with plenty of privacy for romantic dining. For food lovers, The House itself may be one of the best hunting grounds on the island, because the most acclaimed addition to the Barbados restaurant scene is the adjacent Daphne’s. Located bang on the beach, this satellite of the famous London restaurant serves a metropolitan version of Italian dishes, with an emphasis on seafood and is regarded by many as better than the original. Let your Hotel Ambassador organise your complimentary jet-lag massage, a round of golf at nearby Apes Hill Golf Course, spa treatments in a beachside cabana or next door at the sister property Tamarind, or try your hand at the complimentary water sports. The service extends down to the beach and The Deck, with complimentary afternoon tea and evening canapés.

Tivoli Lodge | Vail, Colorado Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Combining modern architecture with the feel of a mountain lodge, the Tivoli is a firm favourite with skiers. Warm in atmosphere with great service from attentive staff, it also enjoys unobstructed views of the Vail’s Golden Peak ski area. Guest rooms are spacious and impeccably-appointed with the finest linens and large soaking tubs – much appreciated after a busy day on the mountain! There are also two hot tubs to stake your place in, both with mountain views, the perfect way to relax and unwind. Breakfast is a delight at the Tivoli, complete with an omelette station and house specialities such as French toast and buttermilk biscuits. Come sundown, there’s the Brown Hound Lounge with overstuffed chairs, leather sofas and towering views of the mountain. A wonderful place for a spot of après-ski, try a signature Indini cocktail, inspired by former mascot Indy, the chocolate Labrador for whom the name is lounged – yep, you guessed it, it has a chocolate theme!

column7: Melia Marina Varadero | Varadero, Cuba Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: This contemporary all-inclusive resort offers a fantastic holiday base overlooking beautiful Varadero beach. Not only does the hotel offer luxury accommodation and amenities galore, there’s lots to enjoy and explore in the surrounding area too, with a promenade just out front and a lively marina with shops, cafés, bars and restaurants — ideal for relaxing awhile and watching the beautiful people go by. It’s also home to a games area with bowling, a diving centre as well as several nightclubs and live music venues — entertainment round the clock then! As well as the beach to stretch out on, you can also grab a good book and throw yourself onto a lounger by one of 3 pools — 2 of them are for especially for children whilst the main pool is lagoon shaped and fun for everyone. Talking of youngsters — they’re going to love it here too. There’s a kids' club with all manner of exciting activities on offer, several play areas and menus tailored especially for them. If you really want to treat yourself — upgrade to rooms on The Level and you’ll enjoy personalised service too, with a VIP bar lounge and guaranteed reservations in the hotel’s a la carte restaurants including the gorgeous Casa Burguete with its vintage glamour.

Moon Palace Jamaica | Ocho Rios, Jamaica Hotel | Virgin Holidays
column13: Occupying centre stage on the largest private beach in Ocho Rios, the Moon Palace Jamaica promises as many sensational sea views as classic Palace Resort touches which is why this is one of the hottest properties in the Caribbean. Consisting of 705 guest rooms, contained within two shimmering towers, you'll be totally spoiled for choice and with four restaurants and six bars to choose from, you certainly won't be left wanting when it comes to a warm welcome. World-class dining options and a tempting gourmet corridor provide a taste of things to come with the excellent Piano Bar offering a world of wine which has been expertly critiqued for your own deliberation. As most guest rooms have fabulous ocean views, fully stocked mini-bars and 24-hour room service, you may prefer to relax in private however, as Family Rooms come with two interconnecting doors you'll be advised to grab the moment while it lasts. Of course, that's not where the fun stops for kids as from their very own pool and FlowRider wave simulator to an organised club and wired teens' lounge, there's plenty of family options to keep your brood happy and active all day long. With four other swimming pools, excellent spa facilities and loads of daily activities, there's never a dull moment and with the stunning Dunn's River Falls just 15-minutes away, getting out and experiencing the very best of Jamaica doesn't get any better than this.
